The paper deals with the problem of decoding binary input discrete memoryless channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses numerical evaluations and theoretical results, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper may fall under the sub-categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) due to its focus on channel coding and decoding.
